+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "TG Daily has an interesting write-up on AMD's
big Q1 loss and [0]how the company plans to get back into the black. AMD
admitted that Q1 was a meltdown and not just a miss. Looks like cost
cutting, including layoffs, may be on the way. But the company says it
won't change its overal direction. The CEO Hector Ruiz is quoted as
saying, 'We are not going to change our strategy because of one lousy
quarter.'"

