| Exhaustive Data Compressor Comparison                              |
|   from the pick-one-smaller-or-faster dept.                        |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday April 22, @22:10 (Software)          |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/22/2039249           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]crazyeyes writes "This is easily the [1]best article I've seen
comparing data compression software. The author tests 11 compressors:
7-zip, ARJ32, bzip2, gzip, SBC Archiver, Squeez, StuffIt, WinAce, WinRAR,
WinRK, and WinZip. All are tested using 8 filesets: audio (WAV and MP3),
documents, e-books, movies (DivX and MPEG), and pictures (PSD and JPEG).
He tests them at different settings and includes the aggregated results.
Spoilers: WinRK gives the best compression but operates slowest; AJR32 is
fastest but compresses least."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/22/2039249

