An anonymous reader writes "When a US legislator describes the Internet
as a 'series of tubes' you just know that you're going to end up with
some wacky laws on the books. Law professor Eric Goldman takes a look at
the [0]best and worst Internet laws in the U.S. Goldman offers an
analysis of the biggies such as the DMCA, but also shines light on
lesser-known laws like the Dot Kids Implementation and Efficiency Act of
2002. And he actually finds four Internet laws that aren't all bad."

